t: In*p my distress I cried unto the Lord,*s and he heard me.
Deliver*p my soul, O Lord,*s from lying lips, and from a deceitful tongue.
What*p shall be given unto thee? or what shall be done unto thee, thou false tongue?
Sharp*p arrows of the mighty, with coals of juniper.
Woe*p is me, that I sojourn in Meshech, that I dwell in the tents of Kedar!
My*p soul hath long dwelt with him that hateth peace.
I*p am for peace: but when I speak, they are for war.
